post_text: Rough night Friday as the lions dropped a pair of JV and varsity games at East Central. Tough way to end the week especially with sick teammates but we look ahead to a big week with road trips to north lakes academy and isle. Time to get back on track this week! Go lions!

post_text: Congrats to the JV girls who pulled off a huge win last night over Mora! Varsity came up short with a 77-58 loss to Mora but we are still growing as a team and the mistakes made are fixable. The Lions have a big conference game at East Central tonight and we hope to bounce back. #nextplay #changingculture

post_text: Varsity girls defeat hinckley 69-52 to start the year off 2-0. FUN FACT....first time ogilvie has started 2-0 since the 2001-2002 season. Congrats ladies!!! Our JV lost a heart breaker 36-40 but they played very hard and the effort is there. Next game: Thursday at Mora!!! Come and support the girls in this renewed rivalry game. Go Lions!!!!

post_text: Welcome players, parents, and fans to our new page! We will keep you up to date on here as far as weekly schedules and happenings in our girls basketball program. Just an FYI for Thanksgiving week, we will practice Friday 8:00 am to 10:00 am. Saturday we leave from Ogilvie to the Mora Jamboree at 12:15 pm. Varsity plays at 1:00 pm and 3:00 pm with the JV playing at 2:00 pm and 4:00 pm. Following the scrimmages we will play half of a game against Milaca with the Varsity tipping of at 6:00 pm and the JV at 6:30 pm. Have a great thanksgiving everyone!!!!
